Yes, that timing works for early next week. Please share when everyone returns to the office and is available.

Following up on the outdoor plan we talked about, I’d start by getting the bed ready and improving the soil. We should turn the ground and mix in compost; the garden center nearby has a fresh organic blend right now. Let’s target Saturday morning if the forecast stays steady. I can bring a few tools from my garage. Also, let’s verify the hardiness zone for those perennials—some may need more light than we expected. I’ll recheck spacing so nothing crowds out later. We may also want to add a simple drip line to conserve water; it’s straightforward and efficient. If you have a moment, please compare mulch types—pine bark or cedar nuggets both look great. I’ll take care of the starter trays. Remember gloves since a couple varieties have thorns. We may need to stake the taller plants once they take off. I’m looking forward to the finished look. Tell me if you want help mapping the layout; I can send a quick sketch. We’ll tweak it as we go. Does that work?

Excited to get started.
Talk soon.

Lowe's

Your Opinion Can Get You an EGO Power+ Leaf Blower.

As a previous Lowe's customer, we'd love to hear how your visit went. After you share your feedback, you'll be set up with an EGO Power+ Leaf Blower plus an $85 Lowe's Store Card.

The EGO Power+ Leaf Blower is a highly rated cordless option with strong airflow and impressive battery performance, helping you tidy up the yard with less hassle. It also fits within the EGO platform, so batteries can be used across compatible tools.

The short set of questions takes under a minute to finish.

Confirmation Code: LWS-MBR-64273

Use this code so we can match your response to the right invitation.

Access Your EGO Blower + $85 Store Card ›

Thanks for helping Lowe's make the experience better for everyone. We value your time and input.

You're receiving this message from Lowe's because it relates to recent customer feedback outreach.

If you prefer not to receive similar messages, you may opt out using the settings provided in your email preferences.

About the team activity, I pulled together a few options based on everyone’s notes. An outdoor picnic is leading, so let’s secure the park space for the coming weeks. We should coordinate meal preferences—I’ll send a quick questionnaire for dietary needs. Also, check whether the company will cover a few games or small rewards. I’ll manage the details like seating and tables. Let’s start closer to midday to keep things simple. Please remind everyone to bring sunscreen and hats. If the weather turns, we already have an indoor backup reserved. I’ll confirm the arrangement with facilities before the end of the week. Let me know if you want to join the setup group. We can split tasks to keep it smooth. I think it’ll be a welcome break for the team. Last year’s responses were great, so we’ll keep the momentum up. We might add a quick icebreaker to begin. Does that sound okay?

Appreciate you helping coordinate.
Best,

Morgan Caldwell

